{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# CKD / GFR Regression Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Predict **GFR** from clinical features.\n",
    "\n",
    "`CKD_Status` is **excluded** from the main feature set.  \n",
    "Chronic kidney disease status is typically defined using GFR thresholds, so using it to predict GFR would be circular / leakage-like.\n",
    "\n",
    "High R² is still expected: **GFR is strongly related to Creatinine** (and similar markers). That is clinically expected, not \"magic ML\".\n",
    "\n",
    "- Target: `GFR`\n",
    "- Features: all columns except `GFR` and `CKD_Status`\n",
    "- Models: Linear Regression vs Gradient Boosting\n",
    "- Split → encode Medication on train only → CV + test metrics\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, KFold, cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingRegressor\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import r2_score, mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error\n",
    "\n",
    "RANDOM_STATE = 42\n",
    "np.random.seed(RANDOM_STATE)\n",
    "\n",
    "DATA_PATH = \"../data/kidney_dataset.csv\"  # if running from notebooks/\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv(DATA_PATH)\n",
    "print(df.shape)\n",
    "display(df.head())\n",
    "df.info()\n",
    "print(\"\\nMissing:\\n\", df.isna().sum())\n",
    "print(\"\\nTarget GFR describe:\\n\", df[\"GFR\"].describe())\n",
    "display(df.corr(numeric_only=True)[[\"GFR\"]].sort_values(\"GFR\"))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "CKD labels are usually derived from GFR stages.  \n",
    "Including `CKD_Status` as a feature when predicting GFR is methodologically unsafe.\n",
    "\n",
    "We still show a quick comparison later, but the **main model excludes it**.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Correlation GFR vs CKD_Status:\", df[[\"GFR\", \"CKD_Status\"]].corr().iloc[0, 1].round(3))\n",
    "print(\"Correlation GFR vs Creatinine:\", df[[\"GFR\", \"Creatinine\"]].corr().iloc[0, 1].round(3))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "TARGET = \"GFR\"\n",
    "DROP_FEATURES = [\"CKD_Status\"]  # excluded on purpose\n",
    "\n",
    "df = df.copy()\n",
    "df[\"Medication\"] = df[\"Medication\"].fillna(\"Unknown\")\n",
    "\n",
    "y = df[TARGET]\n",
    "X = df.drop(columns=[TARGET] + DROP_FEATURES)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "le_med = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "X_train = X_train.copy()\n",
    "X_test = X_test.copy()\n",
    "X_train[\"Medication\"] = le_med.fit_transform(X_train[\"Medication\"].astype(str))\n",
    "\n",
    "known = set(le_med.classes_)\n",
    "X_test[\"Medication\"] = [\n",
    "    int(le_med.transform([v])[0]) if v in known else -1\n",
    "    for v in X_test[\"Medication\"].astype(str)\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(X_train.shape, X_test.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Features:\", list(X_train.columns))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cv = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE)\n",
    "\n",
    "models = {\n",
    "    \"Linear Regression\": LinearRegression(),\n",
    "    \"Gradient Boosting\": GradientBoostingRegressor(random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "rows = []\n",
    "fitted = {}\n",
    "for name, model in models.items():\n",
    "    cv_r2 = cross_val_score(model, X_train, y_train, cv=cv, scoring=\"r2\")\n",
    "    model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "    pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
    "    fitted[name] = (model, pred)\n",
    "    rows.append({\n",
    "        \"Model\": name,\n",
    "        \"CV R2 mean\": cv_r2.mean(),\n",
    "        \"CV R2 std\": cv_r2.std(),\n",
    "        \"Test R2\": r2_score(y_test, pred),\n",
    "        \"Test MAE\": mean_absolute_error(y_test, pred),\n",
    "        \"Test RMSE\": mean_squared_error(y_test, pred) ** 0.5,\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "results = pd.DataFrame(rows).sort_values(\"Test R2\", ascending=False)\n",
    "display(results.round(4))\n",
    "\n",
    "best_name = results.iloc[0][\"Model\"]\n",
    "best_model, best_pred = fitted[best_name]\n",
    "print(\"Best model:\", best_name)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resid = y_test - best_pred\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 4.5))\n",
    "ax.scatter(best_pred, resid, alpha=0.35, s=12)\n",
    "ax.axhline(0, color=\"black\", lw=1)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Predicted GFR\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Residual\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(f\"Residuals — {best_name} (no CKD_Status)\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "if hasattr(best_model, \"feature_importances_\"):\n",
    "    imp = pd.Series(best_model.feature_importances_, index=X_train.columns).sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "    display(imp)\n",
    "    imp.plot(kind=\"barh\", figsize=(7, 4), title=\"Feature importance\")\n",
    "    plt.gca().invert_yaxis()\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    coef = pd.Series(best_model.coef_, index=X_train.columns).sort_values(key=np.abs, ascending=False)\n",
    "    display(coef)\n",
    "    print(\"Linear coefficients (sorted by |value|)\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "Train the same Linear Regression **with** `CKD_Status` only to show the difference.  \n",
    "Final model remains **without** `CKD_Status`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_leak = df.drop(columns=[TARGET]).copy()\n",
    "X_leak[\"Medication\"] = LabelEncoder().fit_transform(X_leak[\"Medication\"].astype(str))\n",
    "Xl_tr, Xl_te, yl_tr, yl_te = train_test_split(X_leak, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE)\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_leak = LinearRegression().fit(Xl_tr, yl_tr)\n",
    "pred_leak = lr_leak.predict(Xl_te)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Test R2 WITHOUT CKD_Status (Linear):\", round(results.loc[results[\"Model\"]==\"Linear Regression\", \"Test R2\"].values[0], 4))\n",
    "print(\"Test R2 WITH CKD_Status (Linear):   \", round(r2_score(yl_te, pred_leak), 4))\n",
    "print(\"Conclusion: CKD_Status is excluded from the final pipeline.\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "1. Final features exclude `CKD_Status` to avoid circularity with GFR.\n",
    "2. High R² is largely explained by the strong Creatinine–GFR relationship.\n",
    "3. Gradient Boosting / Linear Regression are compared with CV + holdout test.\n",
    "4. Encoding of `Medication` is fit on train only.\n",
    "5. This is an educational analysis, not a clinical diagnostic tool.\n"
   ]
  }
 ],
